-- Factbox: Moody's downgrades global banks
-- 
-- Thu Jun 21, 2012 11:23pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/22/us-financial-moodys-table-idUSBRE85K1VY20120622

 

 (Reuters) - Credit ratings agency Moody's downgraded 15 global banks on Thursday after a months-long review. Below is a summary of old and new long-term ratings for the bank holding companies and operating companies (including two downgraded earlier this year). 
 Bank Name	                    New Rating	Old Rating Bank of America	            Baa2	              Baa1 Barclays	                          A3	               A1 BNP Paribas	                          A2	              Aa3 Citigroup	                        Baa2	              A3 Credit Agricole S.A.	             A2	             Aa3 Credit Suisse	                         A1***	             Aa1 Deutsche Bank	             A2	             Aa3 Goldman Sachs	             A3	              A1 HSBC Holdings	            Aa3	            Aa2 JP Morgan Chase	             A2	            Aa3 Macquarie	                         A3*	            A2 Morgan Stanley	            Baa1	            A2 Nomura Holdings	            Baa3**	Baa2 Royal Bank of Canada	Aa3	            Aa1 Royal Bank of Scotland	Baa1	            A3 Societe Generale	            A2	            A1 UBS	                                    A2	          Aa3 * Moody's downgraded Macquarie Group Ltd. to A3 on March 16 from a previous rating of A2 ** Moody's downgraded Nomura Holdings, Inc. to Baa3 on March 15 from a previous rating of Baa2 *** Moody's downgraded Credit Suisse Group AG (the holding company) provisional senior debt to (P)A2 from (P)Aa2, outlook stable. (Reporting by Sam Forgione and  Daniel Bases ; Editing by  Gary Hill  and Carol Bishopric)